item.title: Grand Produits
item.dc:creator: demo
item.content:encoded:
Theatre (or theater, see spelling differences) is a branch of the performing arts. Any performance may be considered theatre; however, as a performing art, theatre focuses almost exclusively on live performers enacting a self-contained drama before an audience.[1] A performance qualifies as dramatic by creating a representational illusion.[2] The word "theatre" derives from the Ancient Greek theatron (θέατρον) meaning "a place for viewing."[3] A theatrical performance may include music, dance and various elements of stagecraft such as costumes, sets, lights, stage properties and sound engineering, among others.
Modern Western theatre derives in large measure from ancient Greek drama, from which it borrows technical terminology, classification into genres, and many of its themes, stock characters, and plot elements. Theatre scholar Patrice Pavis defines theatricality,theatrical language, stage writing, and the specificity of theatre as synonymous expressions that differentiate theatre from the other performing arts, literature, and the arts in general.[4] Theatre includes performances of plays and musicals. Although it can be defined broadly to include opera and ballet, those art forms are outside the scope of this article.

item.title: How It Works
item.dc:creator: demo
item.content:encoded: We're your one-stop-shop for online daily deals! Sign Up! Visit us and enter your name and email address. That’s all you have to do to sign up. Also, be sure to ‘like’ our Facebook page to get information about special giveaways and promotions. Check Your Email! Each time a new deal is available you will receive an email. These deals could be to local restaurants, golf courses, bowling alleys, movie theaters or any other local business. The deals are typically between 40-75% off! Buy Em’ or Trash Em’! If you see a deal you like simply click buy. If the deal doesn’t spark your interest, just delete it. Purchasing the deal is simple and the printable voucher will remain in your account until you’re ready to redeDealt! Work the Deal! When you’re deal to use your deal simply sign in to your account, print off the voucher and present it at the business. That’s all there is to it!

item.title: Share and Earn
item.dc:creator: demo
item.content:encoded:
Did you know that you don’t have to spend any money to earn credits? That’s right, simply use our quick share buttons to tell your friends, family and co-workers about Perks they may be interested in. When someone buys after you’ve shared it with them you earn a site reward! How’s it work? Find the share icone and click on the quick share links. Follow the instructions below for detailed instructions on how to share. Remember:
  1. You must register an account before your site rewards can be properly assigned.
  2. You must be signed into your account before using the share links.
